Subject: Buying power from Industrials

Below is information about a FERC order allowing a power marketer, like EES=20
or EPMI, to file to effectively act as an industrials "agent" when buying an=
=20
industrial's excess power to insert into the grid.  Generally, an industrial=
=20
would be required to obtain its own FERC power marketer license (takes about=
=20
60 days) in order to sell into the grid.  EPMI and EES have not requested th=
e=20
"Impower" type agent authority yet, but I have been asked to file this for=20
EPMI (and, Dennis, we could file for EES too, let me know).=20

If FERC allows EPMI and EES to do this, then we would make quarterly filings=
=20
on behalf of any industrials from whom we buy power at wholesale and they=20
would not have to make their own FERC power marketer filings.  (Also, Enron=20
generally has to also file for "EWG" Exempt Wholesale Generator status due t=
o=20
utility rules; however, if the industrial is primarily an industrial busines=
s=20
in something other than power generation, an EWG determination is not=20
required.)

I will keep you advised on the status of the filing(s) once made.

